headline: WST Q1 Earnings Call: Revenue Guidance Raised, Margins Impacted by Product Mix and Tariffs
summary: Healthcare products company West Pharmaceutical Services (NYSE:WST) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q1 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $698 million. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $2.96 billion at the midpoint came in 1.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.45 per share was 15.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
